eas_text: A civil authority has issued A CHILD ABDUCTION EMERGENCY for the following counties or areas: Minnesota; at 10:34 PM ON JAN 21, 2026 Effective until 11:34 PM. Message from WSLF/CAP.
extra_text: This is a coordinated Minnesota Amber Alert. This is a missing or abducted child alert. We interrupt this program to bring you this time sensitive message. The Sherburne County Sheriff's Office is searching for a missing or abducted 7 year old white female named Brynlee Nelson.  Brynlee is 4 feet 3 inches tall, weighs 70 pounds, with hazel eyes and blonde hair. She was last seen wearing a black jacket, white boots and blue snow pants, carrying a backpack with keychains and trinkets. She was wearing a pink sweatshirt and black pants underneath the winter clothing and was last seen near the 26000 block of 13th Street West in Zimmerman.  If you have any information regarding this missing child, call the Sherburne County Sheriff's Office at 7 6 3 7 6 5 3 5 9 5 or 9 1 1. Anyone who may locate Brynlee should contact the police as soon as possible. Stay tuned for further instructions.
